---
allowed-tools: Read, Write, Bash, Glob, Grep
description: Review or generate UX/UI design spec for a feature or screen
---

Design review for: $ARGUMENTS

## Step 1: Survey existing design artifacts

Check what design infrastructure exists in this project:

```bash
# Design system / component library
grep -E '"@shadcn|@mui|@chakra-ui|@radix-ui|@headlessui|antd|mantine' package.json 2>/dev/null

# Design tokens
ls tokens.json design-tokens/ style-dictionary.config.* tailwind.config.* 2>/dev/null

# Storybook
ls .storybook/ storybook.config.* 2>/dev/null

# Figma references
grep -rn "figma.com" . --include="*.md" --include="*.json" --include="*.ts" 2>/dev/null | head -10
```

Report what was found before proceeding.

## Step 2: Invoke the design agent

Hand off to the `design` agent with full context:
- The feature or screen from $ARGUMENTS (or all recently modified UI files if empty)
- All design artifacts detected in Step 1
- Instruction to cover all 4 review areas

## Step 3: Save output

Save the design review to `specs/design-[feature-name].md` with this structure:

```markdown
# Design Review: [Feature]

## Design Artifacts Found
[tools, tokens, libraries, Figma links]

## 1. UI/UX Review
[visual hierarchy, spacing, flow, consistency with existing screens]

## 2. Design System
[token usage, component reuse, deviations from the system]

## 3. Component Architecture
[props API, composition, naming, reusability]

## 4. Accessibility
[ARIA, contrast, keyboard nav, focus management, screen reader]

## Issues
| Severity | Area | Description | File |
|----------|------|-------------|------|
| 🔴 Critical | ... | ... | ... |
| 🟡 Warning  | ... | ... | ... |
| 🟢 Suggestion | ... | ... | ... |

## Recommendations
[ordered by priority]
```
